2.4.7 - Grficos de Barra

Questo 1

base <- 
  tibble(
    "rea do conhecimento" = c("Sade", "Exatas", "Humanas", "Comunicao"),
    "Instituio A" = c(1751, 2186, 947,  29),
    "Instituio B" = c(2528, 2132, 1843, 280)
  )

base %<>% mutate("Relao B com A" = `Instituio B`/`Instituio A`)

barplot(
  base$`Relao B com A`, names.arg = base$`rea do conhecimento`,
  main = "Relao Instituio B/A", ylab = "rea do Conhecimento"
)

Questo 2

Questo 9

base_cotinina <- 
  tibble(
    "Nvel de Cotinina (ng/ml)" = c("0-13", "14-49", "50-99", "100-149", "150-199", "200-249", "250-299", "300+"),
    Fumantes = c(78,133,142,206,197,220,151,412),
    "No-fumantes" = c(3300,72,23,15,7,8,9,11)
  )

matrix(
  c(base_cotinina$Fumantes, base_cotinina$`No-fumantes`), ncol = 2,
  dimnames = list(base_cotinina$`Nvel de Cotinina (ng/ml)`, c("Fumantes", "No-fumantes"))
) %>% 
  t %>% 
  barplot(
    beside = T, cex.names = 0.9, legend.text = c("Fumantes", "No-fumantes"),
    xlab = "Nvel de Cotinina (ng/ml)", ylab = "Frequncia",
    main = "Frequncia do nvel de cotinina em fumantes e no-fumantes",
    col = c("#000000", "#5F021F")
  )

2.10.1 - Grfico da distribuio normal

Questo 1

catalisador <- c(1176, 1191, 1214, 1220, 1205, 1192, 1201, 1190, 1183, 1185)
curve(dnorm(x, mean = mean(catalisador), sd = sd(catalisador)), 
      from=mean(catalisador)-50, to=mean(catalisador)+50, 
      xlab = "x", ylab = "dnorm(x, mean(catalisador), sd(catalisador))",
      main = "Distribuio normal do tempo efetivo de vida \n de um catalisador usado em reaes qumicas")

Questo 2

curve(dnorm(x, mean=  -1, sd=1), from=-5, to=5)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=-0.5, sd=1), col="red", add=T)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=   0, sd=1), col="green", add=T)
curve(dnorm(x, mean= 0.5, sd=1), col="blue", add=T)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=   1, sd=1), col="yellow", add=T)
title("Distribuio normal variando a mdia no intervalo [-1,1] \n com tamanho de passo igual a 0.5 e desvio padro igual a 1")

Questo 3

curve(dnorm(x, mean=0, sd=  0), col="red", from=-5, to=5)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=0, sd=0.5), add=T)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=0, sd=  1), col="green", add=T)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=0, sd=1.5), col="blue", add=T)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=0, sd=  2), col="yellow", add=T)
title("Distribuio normal variando o desvio padro no intervalo [0,2] \n com tamanho de passo igual a 0.5 e mdia igual a 0")

Questo 4

pesos <- c(0.9475,0.9705,0.9770,0.9775,0.9860,0.9960,0.9965,0.9975,1.0050,1.0075,1.0100,1.0175,1.0180,1.02000,1.0250)

hist(pesos, freq=FALSE)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=1, sd=0.05), add=TRUE, col=4)
curve(dnorm(x, mean=mean(pesos), sd=sd(pesos)), add=TRUE, col="red")
legend('topright', legend=c(expression(mu==1),  expression(sigma==0.05),
                            expression(mu==0.997), expression(sigma==0.022)), 
       text.col=c(4,4,2,2), cex=0.8)
